com.bmd.android.collection.entry

Interface SimpleArrayMapEntry<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type.
    V - the value type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    ObjectSparseEntry<K>, ObjectSparseObjectEntry<K,V>, SparseEntry, SparseObjectEntry<V>

    public interface SimpleArrayMapEntry<K,V>
extends ObjectSparseObjectEntry<K,V>
    This interface defines a SparseEntry associated with a SimpleArrayMap collection.

    Created by davide on 3/10/14.

      • toImmutable

        ObjectSparseObjectEntry<K,V> toImmutable()
        Returns an immutable copy of this entry. The object will just store this entry key and value without allowing any modification of the backing array map.
        Returns:
        the immutable entry.

      • toParcelable

        ParcelableObjectSparseObjectEntry<K,V> toParcelable()
        Returns a parcelable copy of this entry. The object will just store this entry key and value without allowing any modification of the backing array map.

        Note that the Parcel.writeValue(Object) function will be called to serialize the entry key and value. So, if any of the two does not comply with the specific requirements, the serialization might have unexpected results.

        Returns:
        the parcelable entry.
